<h2>Conclusion</h2>
<p>
And finally, the message of this post is:
<ul class="emp_result">
    <li>The Wilks normalization is much more fair than normalization according to the body weight or no normalization. It works well especially for women.</li>
    <li>The Wilks normalization seems to work also for single lifts, especially for men and women deadlift, women benchpress and women squat.</li>
    <li>The normalization according to the body weight is better than no normalization.</li>
</ul>
</p>



 




